{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"gpu","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":125222}],"dockerImageVersionId":31401,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"md-intro","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Stellar Classification (PS S6E6) — GPU Stacking Pipeline\n\n**Design goals**\n- Train on the *actual* competition train data — no leaked/blended public submissions.\n- GPU-native boosters (XGBoost `device=cuda`, LightGBM `device=gpu`, CatBoost `task_type=GPU`) so the whole pipeline runs in minutes on a T4.\n- Physics-informed features from SDSS photometry: color indices, magnitude ratios, redshift transforms — these are the real signal in GALAXY/QSO/STAR separation, not row-flipping.\n- 5-fold stratified CV everywhere, OOF predictions used for an honest stacking blend (Nelder-Mead weight search on OOF logloss/accuracy, not on public-LB-derived files).\n- Pseudo-labeling pass on high-confidence test rows, re-fit, single clean `submission.csv`.\n\nIf a GPU isn't available, every model below has a CPU fallback so the notebook still runs end-to-end.","metadata":{}},{"id":"cell-00-setup","cell_type":"code","source":"import os, sys, time, warnings, gc\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, log_loss\nfrom scipy.optimize import minimize\n\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\npd.set_option('display.max_columns', 100)\n\nSEED = 42\nN_FOLDS = 5\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\n\n# ── GPU detection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndef detect_gpu():\n    try:\n        import subprocess\n        out = subprocess.run(['nvidia-smi'], capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=5)\n        return out.returncode == 0\n    except Exception:\n        return False\n\nGPU = detect_gpu()\nprint(f'GPU available: {GPU}')\nif GPU:\n    os.system('nvidia-smi --query-gpu=name,memory.total --format=csv,noheader')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T07:56:26.253161Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T07:56:26.253419Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-29T07:56:28.86008Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-29T07:56:26.253387Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-29T07:56:28.859232Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"GPU available: True\nTesla P100-PCIE-16GB, 16384 MiB\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":1},{"id":"cell-01-load","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Load data ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nDATA_DIR = '/kaggle/input/competitions/playground-series-s6e6'\n\ntrain = pd.read_csv(f'{DATA_DIR}/train.csv')\ntest  = pd.read_csv(f'{DATA_DIR}/test.csv')\n\nID, TARGET = 'id', 'class'\nLABELS = sorted(train[TARGET].unique())\nprint('Classes:', LABELS)\n\nle = LabelEncoder().fit(train[TARGET])\ny_full = le.transform(train[TARGET])\n\nprint('Train shape:', train.shape)\nprint('Test shape :', test.shape)\ntrain.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-29T07:56:28.861916Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-29T07:56:28.862708Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"md-features","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Physics-informed feature engineering\n\nSDSS photometry gives five magnitude bands (`u, g, r, i, z`) plus `redshift`, plate/MJD/fiber metadata, and derived RA/Dec. The features that actually separate STAR / GALAXY / QSO physically are:\n\n- **Color indices** (`u-g, g-r, r-i, i-z, u-z`) — these trace the spectral energy distribution shape; quasars and stars occupy very different loci in color-color space than galaxies.\n- **Redshift transforms** — galaxies and especially quasars have measurable redshift; stars (same galaxy) cluster near `redshift ≈ 0`. Log/sign/binned transforms help tree models split cleanly.\n- **Magnitude ratios & sums** — total brightness and band ratios add information beyond raw magnitudes alone.\n- **PCA color axis** — SDSS's own `u-g` vs `g-r` star/galaxy/QSO locus separation, approximated via a rotated color-color combination.\n\nThis cell only uses columns that exist in the dataframe — if a column is missing it's skipped safely.","metadata":{}},{"id":"cell-02-fe","cell_type":"code","source":"BANDS = ['u', 'g', 'r', 'i', 'z']\n\ndef add_physics_features(df):\n    df = df.copy()\n    present = [b for b in BANDS if b in df.columns]\n\n    # Color indices (adjacent + cross bands)\n    for a, b in zip(present, present[1:]):\n        df[f'{a}_{b}_color'] = df[a] - df[b]\n    if 'u' in present and 'z' in present:\n        df['u_z_color'] = df['u'] - df['z']\n    if 'g' in present and 'i' in present:\n        df['g_i_color'] = df['g'] - df['i']\n\n    # Aggregate brightness stats\n    if len(present) >= 3:\n        df['mag_mean'] = df[present].mean(axis=1)\n        df['mag_std']  = df[present].std(axis=1)\n        df['mag_range'] = df[present].max(axis=1) - df[present].min(axis=1)\n        df['mag_sum'] = df[present].sum(axis=1)\n\n    # Pairwise ratios for the strongest discriminating bands\n    if 'u' in present and 'g' in present:\n        df['u_g_ratio'] = df['u'] / (df['g'].replace(0, np.nan))\n    if 'r' in present and 'i' in present:\n        df['r_i_ratio'] = df['r'] / (df['i'].replace(0, np.nan))\n\n    # Redshift transforms — primary QSO/GALAXY vs STAR separator\n    if 'redshift' in df.columns:\n        df['redshift_abs'] = df['redshift'].abs()\n        df['redshift_log1p'] = np.sign(df['redshift']) * np.log1p(df['redshift'].abs())\n        df['redshift_is_near_zero'] = (df['redshift'].abs() < 1e-3).astype(np.int8)\n        df['redshift_sq'] = df['redshift'] ** 2\n        # Color-redshift interactions (color evolves with redshift for galaxies/QSOs)\n        if 'g_r_color' in df.columns:\n            df['color_x_redshift'] = df['g_r_color'] * df['redshift']\n\n    # Rotated color-color axis approximating the SDSS star/galaxy/QSO locus split\n    if 'u_g_color' in df.columns and 'g_r_color' in df.columns:\n        theta = np.deg2rad(35)\n        df['locus_axis1'] = (df['u_g_color'] * np.cos(theta) + df['g_r_color'] * np.sin(theta))\n        df['locus_axis2'] = (-df['u_g_color'] * np.sin(theta) + df['g_r_color'] * np.cos(theta))\n\n    # Positional features (some objects cluster spatially by survey plate)\n    if 'plate' in df.columns:\n        df['plate_mod'] = df['plate'] % 100\n    if 'fiber_id' in df.columns:\n        df['fiber_log'] = np.log1p(df['fiber_id'])\n\n    df.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan, inplace=True)\n    return df\n\ntrain_fe = add_physics_features(train)\ntest_fe  = add_physics_features(test)\n\ndrop_cols = [ID, TARGET]\nfeature_cols = [c for c in train_fe.columns if c not in drop_cols]\nfeature_cols = [c for c in feature_cols if train_fe[c].dtype != object]\n\nprint(f'Total engineered features: {len(feature_cols)}')\nprint(feature_cols)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cell-03-matrices","cell_type":"code","source":"X = train_fe[feature_cols].copy()\nX_test = test_fe[feature_cols].copy()\n\n# Fill NaNs introduced by ratios/logs with column median (fit on train only)\nmedians = X.median()\nX = X.fillna(medians)\nX_test = X_test.fillna(medians)\n\nprint('X shape:', X.shape, '| X_test shape:', X_test.shape)\nfolds = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=N_FOLDS, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED)\nfold_idx = list(folds.split(X, y_full))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"md-models","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## GPU model zoo\n\nThree boosters, each GPU-native with a CPU fallback so the notebook degrades gracefully if no GPU is attached:\n\n| Model | GPU flag | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| XGBoost | `device='cuda'`, `tree_method='hist'` | Fastest on T4 for this row count |\n| LightGBM | `device='gpu'` | Falls back to `device='cpu'` automatically if GPU build unavailable |\n| CatBoost | `task_type='GPU'` | Handles categorical-ish integer columns (plate/fiber) natively |\n\nEach model is trained with 5-fold CV, producing out-of-fold (OOF) probability predictions for honest stacking, plus averaged test predictions across folds.","metadata":{}},{"id":"cell-04-state","cell_type":"code","source":"N_CLASSES = len(LABELS)\noof_preds = {}\ntest_preds = {}\nfold_scores = {}","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cell-05-xgb-params","cell_type":"code","source":"import xgboost as xgb\n\nxgb_params = dict(\n    objective='multi:softprob',\n    num_class=N_CLASSES,\n    eval_metric='mlogloss',\n    max_depth=8,\n    learning_rate=0.03,\n    n_estimators=3000,\n    subsample=0.85,\n    colsample_bytree=0.85,\n    min_child_weight=4,\n    reg_lambda=1.5,\n    reg_alpha=0.1,\n    random_state=SEED,\n)\nif GPU:\n    xgb_params.update(device='cuda', tree_method='hist')\nelse:\n    xgb_params.update(tree_method='hist')\n\nprint('XGBoost params ready. GPU mode:', GPU)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cell-06-runner","cell_type":"code","source":"# run_oof_v2: each fold's y_val is available directly inside the loop,\n# so build_model_fn(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val) can use early stopping correctly.\n\ndef run_oof_v2(name, build_model_fn):\n    \"\"\"build_model_fn(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val) -> fitted model with .predict_proba\"\"\"\n    oof = np.zeros((len(X), N_CLASSES))\n    test_p = np.zeros((len(X_test), N_CLASSES))\n    t0 = time.time()\n    for fold, (tr_idx, val_idx) in enumerate(fold_idx):\n        X_tr, X_val = X.iloc[tr_idx], X.iloc[val_idx]\n        y_tr, y_val = y_full[tr_idx], y_full[val_idx]\n        model = build_model_fn(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val)\n        val_p = model.predict_proba(X_val)\n        te_p  = model.predict_proba(X_test)\n        oof[val_idx] = val_p\n        test_p += te_p / N_FOLDS\n        acc = accuracy_score(y_val, val_p.argmax(1))\n        print(f'  [{name}] fold {fold+1}/{N_FOLDS}  acc={acc:.5f}')\n    elapsed = time.time() - t0\n    overall_acc = accuracy_score(y_full, oof.argmax(1))\n    print(f'[{name}] OOF acc = {overall_acc:.5f}   ({elapsed:.1f}s total)\\n')\n    oof_preds[name] = oof\n    test_preds[name] = test_p\n    fold_scores[name] = overall_acc\n    return oof, test_p\n\n\ndef build_xgb(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val):\n    model = xgb.XGBClassifier(**xgb_params, early_stopping_rounds=100)\n    model.fit(X_tr, y_tr, eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)], verbose=False)\n    return model\n\nrun_oof_v2('xgb', build_xgb)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cell-07-lgbm","cell_type":"code","source":"import lightgbm as lgb\n\nlgbm_params = dict(\n    objective='multiclass',\n    num_class=N_CLASSES,\n    metric='multi_logloss',\n    max_depth=-1,\n    num_leaves=255,\n    learning_rate=0.03,\n    n_estimators=3000,\n    subsample=0.85,\n    colsample_bytree=0.85,\n    min_child_samples=20,\n    reg_lambda=1.5,\n    reg_alpha=0.1,\n    random_state=SEED,\n    verbosity=-1,\n)\nif GPU:\n    lgbm_params.update(device='gpu')\n\ndef build_lgbm(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val):\n    params = dict(lgbm_params)\n    try:\n        model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(**params)\n        model.fit(\n            X_tr, y_tr,\n            eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)],\n            callbacks=[lgb.early_stopping(100, verbose=False)],\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        # GPU build not available in this environment — fall back to CPU\n        print(f'    (LightGBM GPU failed: {e} — falling back to CPU)')\n        params['device'] = 'cpu'\n        model = lgb.LGBMClassifier(**params)\n        model.fit(\n            X_tr, y_tr,\n            eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)],\n            callbacks=[lgb.early_stopping(100, verbose=False)],\n        )\n    return model\n\nrun_oof_v2('lgbm', build_lgbm)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cell-08-catboost","cell_type":"code","source":"from catboost import CatBoostClassifier\n\ncat_params = dict(\n    loss_function='MultiClass',\n    eval_metric='MultiClass',\n    depth=8,\n    learning_rate=0.03,\n    iterations=3000,\n    l2_leaf_reg=3.0,\n    random_seed=SEED,\n    verbose=False,\n)\nif GPU:\n    cat_params.update(task_type='GPU', devices='0')\n\ndef build_cat(X_tr, y_tr, X_val, y_val):\n    params = dict(cat_params)\n    try:\n        model = CatBoostClassifier(**params, early_stopping_rounds=100)\n        model.fit(X_tr, y_tr, eval_set=(X_val, y_val), use_best_model=True, verbose=False)\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f'    (CatBoost GPU failed: {e} — falling back to CPU)')\n        params['task_type'] = 'CPU'\n        params.pop('devices', None)\n        model = CatBoostClassifier(**params, early_stopping_rounds=100)\n        model.fit(X_tr, y_tr, eval_set=(X_val, y_val), use_best_model=True, verbose=False)\n    return model\n\nrun_oof_v2('cat', build_cat)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"md-stack","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Honest stacking — Nelder-Mead weights fit on OOF, not on leaked files\n\nThis is the same Nelder-Mead idea from your earlier pipelines, but applied correctly: weights are optimized against **out-of-fold predictions on the real train labels**, so the blend generalizes instead of overfitting to a public-LB artifact.","metadata":{}},{"id":"cell-09-blend","cell_type":"code","source":"model_names = list(oof_preds.keys())\nprint('Individual OOF accuracies:')\nfor n in model_names:\n    print(f'  {n:6s}: {fold_scores[n]:.5f}')\n\ndef blend_neg_acc(w):\n    w = np.abs(w)\n    w = w / w.sum()\n    blended = sum(wi * oof_preds[n] for wi, n in zip(w, model_names))\n    return -accuracy_score(y_full, blended.argmax(1))\n\nx0 = np.ones(len(model_names)) / len(model_names)\nres = minimize(blend_neg_acc, x0, method='Nelder-Mead',\n                options={'maxiter': 2000, 'xatol': 1e-6, 'fatol': 1e-6})\n\nbest_w = np.abs(res.x)\nbest_w = best_w / best_w.sum()\nprint('\\nOptimized blend weights:')\nfor n, w in zip(model_names, best_w):\n    print(f'  {n:6s}: {w:.4f}')\n\noof_blend = sum(w * oof_preds[n] for w, n in zip(best_w, model_names))\nblend_acc = accuracy_score(y_full, oof_blend.argmax(1))\nprint(f'\\nBlended OOF accuracy: {blend_acc:.5f}')\n\ntest_blend = sum(w * test_preds[n] for w, n in zip(best_w, model_names))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"md-pseudo","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Pseudo-labeling pass\n\nAdd high-confidence test predictions (margin between top-1 and top-2 class probability above a threshold) back into the training set, then refit XGBoost (fastest of the three) once more for a final confidence boost. This only uses the model's own calibrated confidence — no external file scores involved.","metadata":{}},{"id":"cell-10-pseudo","cell_type":"code","source":"sorted_probs = np.sort(test_blend, axis=1)\nmargin = sorted_probs[:, -1] - sorted_probs[:, -2]\nCONF_THRESH = 0.90\n\nconfident_mask = margin > CONF_THRESH\nn_confident = confident_mask.sum()\nprint(f'High-confidence pseudo-label candidates (margin > {CONF_THRESH}): {n_confident} / {len(test_blend)}')\n\nif n_confident > 0:\n    pseudo_X = X_test.loc[confident_mask]\n    pseudo_y = test_blend[confident_mask].argmax(1)\n\n    X_aug = pd.concat([X, pseudo_X], axis=0).reset_index(drop=True)\n    y_aug = np.concatenate([y_full, pseudo_y])\n\n    print('Refitting final XGBoost on augmented data (train + pseudo-labeled test)...')\n    final_folds = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=N_FOLDS, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED + 1)\n    final_test_p = np.zeros((len(X_test), N_CLASSES))\n    for fold, (tr_idx, val_idx) in enumerate(final_folds.split(X_aug, y_aug)):\n        X_tr, X_val = X_aug.iloc[tr_idx], X_aug.iloc[val_idx]\n        y_tr, y_val = y_aug[tr_idx], y_aug[val_idx]\n        model = xgb.XGBClassifier(**xgb_params, early_stopping_rounds=100)\n        model.fit(X_tr, y_tr, eval_set=[(X_val, y_val)], verbose=False)\n        final_test_p += model.predict_proba(X_test) / N_FOLDS\n        acc = accuracy_score(y_val, model.predict_proba(X_val).argmax(1))\n        print(f'  pseudo-fold {fold+1}/{N_FOLDS}  acc={acc:.5f}')\n\n    # Average the pseudo-labeled refit with the original blend for stability\n    final_probs = 0.5 * final_test_p + 0.5 * test_blend\nelse:\n    print('No candidates above threshold — using blend predictions as final.')\n    final_probs = test_blend","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"cell-11-submit","cell_type":"code","source":"final_pred_idx = final_probs.argmax(1)\nfinal_labels = le.inverse_transform(final_pred_idx)\n\nsubmission = pd.DataFrame({ID: test[ID], TARGET: final_labels})\nsubmission.to_csv('submission.csv', index=False)\n\nprint('submission.csv saved.')\nprint(submission[TARGET].value_counts())\nsubmission.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"id":"md-notes","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Notes / next tuning steps\n\n- **Runtime**: on a T4, this full pipeline (3 boosters × 5 folds + pseudo-label refit) typically finishes in well under 15 minutes for Playground-sized data (sub-1M rows). If LightGBM's GPU build isn't installed in your environment it auto-falls-back to CPU — check the printed message after that cell.\n- **If OOF accuracy plateaus**, the highest-leverage next steps are usually: (1) tighten `CONF_THRESH` upward if pseudo-labeling isn't helping, (2) add a small neural net (TabM/RealMLP) as a 4th stacking member for diversity, (3) inspect OOF confusion matrix for GALAXY/QSO boundary errors and add targeted redshift-bin × color interaction features there.\n- **Do not** swap this back to blending public submission CSVs by filename score — that path doesn't generalize to the private leaderboard and was removed intentionally.","metadata":{}}]}